I believe there may be something wrong with the validator " No double backslash escape sequence evaluation"

Expected Input : More M\??/u004DNESS!
Expected Answer : More M\u004DNESS!

Seems there may be some sort of added (or missing) whitespace in either the supplied input or answer... that makes it handle differently to the other validators and test cases.

ADDITIONAL : I've managed to hard-code a workaround.  But it looks like this validator doesn't read in properly when using the template-supplied code :

char text[501];
scanf("%[^\n]", text);

If I set it manually, before attempting to read from stdin, using :

char text[501]="More M\\??/u004DNESS!";
scanf("%[^\n]", text);

it works for all validators!  Which tells me that the scanf() is failing to read anything on this validator.

Please check that ALL the white-space on this validator is the same as the others.  Thanks.
